    "updated_at": "2015-11-18T18:32:13Z",
    "body": "Makes sense. Didn't realize session could outlive the window.\n\nSo what's the best way to handle this? Currently, I'm listening to the window `close` event, but it's a bit verbose: https://github.com/sindresorhus/electron-dl/blob/506344214659e732ad7685ca499ced82085304bc/index.js#L21-L23\n\nMaybe we could have a way to check if a window is still available to use. Like: `BrowserWindow#isOpen` or something?\n"
